cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with computation rates and coding schemes, which are key concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless sensor networks and network models, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses scheduling of concurrent transmissions, which is a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the broadcast and superposition properties of wireless channels, which are relevant to multimedia communication. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with computing functions of sensor measurements, which can be seen as a data processing problem.
